San Francisco Salaries EDA¶

Brief info on dataset¶

* This data contains the names, job title, and compensation for San Francisco city employees on an annual basis from    2011 to 2014.
* We can observe -
    * How salaries have changed over time between different jobs
    * Number of Jobs per Year.
    * The average salary of employees per year.
    * The top 5 most common jobs.
    * Compare Jobs with high salaries and TotalPay(with overtimepay etc).
    * Compare Jobs with high salaries and TotalPayBenefits.
    * Compare high OvertimePaying Jobs.

In [44]:
# Function to get the average basepay for the top 5 most common jobs from the list

def get_avgpay2(df, col, titles, avgcol, yearcol, years):
    if isinstance(titles, str):
        # if titles is a single string, convert it to a list
        titles = [titles]
    results = [] # create a results list
    for title in titles:
        # check if the job title is in the DataFrame, regardless of case
        if not any(df[col].str.lower() == title.lower()):
            print(f"Job title '{title}' not found in DataFrame") # prints if the job isnt found in the dataframe
            continue
        result = {'JobTitle': title} 
        for year in years:
            avg_year = df[(df[col].str.lower() == title.lower()) & (df[yearcol] == year)][avgcol].mean() # get average of title column for given year
            result[str(year)] = avg_year # store average base pay for year in result dictionary
            
        avg = df[df[col].str.lower() == title.lower()][avgcol].mean() # get overall average of title column
        result['Avg_Total_basepay'] = avg # store job title and overall average base pay
        
        results.append(result) # add result dictionary to list    
    return pd.DataFrame(results) # convert list of dictionaries to dataframe

In Conclusion¶

  • The Average BasePay through years 2011 - 2014 is approximately 66,100 For all Jobs.
  • GARY JIMENEZ is employee with most overtimepay and is the Captain III of Police.
  • The most common job is a Transit Operator with average Basepay of 51,500.
  • We have no Correlation between Job Title string and Salary.
  • The number of job entries increase as the year increases.
  • There is a huge differnce between the BasePay for Jobs and the TotalPay - Highest BasePay job is Chief of Police and Highest TotalPay job is General manager of Transit Authority.
  • Your Totalpay gotten and can be higher than other workers basepay depending on extra effort put into work.
  • The least paying jobs are probably those who spent more than supposed to or owe the company hence the negative values.
  • Most Junior clerk jobs have the least paid jobs as their basepay is in the negatives.
  • Chief Investment officer is the job with the highest paying benefits.

Decision¶

  • Looking for high benefits? take a job as a chief investment officer
  • Like working overtime? with good pay?. Take a job as the Captain III of police
  • Like working with good pay, benefits or not and without extra effort? Then take a job as the General Manager of Transit Authority
  • Looking for a community based job with lots of people in it? then take a job as a Transit Operator
